modules.description: This module manages file paths and directory creation for a zoo-based data processing system. It provides functions to construct paths using a base directory and hash table identifier, create temporary directories with specific permissions, and generate paths for remote resources like gists. These operations are used when organizing and accessing versioned data files in distributed environments.

Registers a custom directive "zoo" in the OCaml toploop, enabling interactive use of Owl's zoo system for loading pre-trained models and datasets directly in the REPL. Works with the OCaml runtime environment and toploop initialization. Useful for quickly testing and experimenting with Owl models without requiring manual module loading.

This module provides commands to manage and execute OCaml scripts stored as gists, including uploading, downloading, listing, and updating gist-based bundles. It supports operations on local and remote gist repositories, enabling users to run scripts directly from gists with specified arguments. Key data types include gist identifiers, script paths, and versioned bundles, used in workflows like executing machine learning models or numerical computations from shared gists.

This module manages version records for gists in a local zoo repository, providing operations to check existence, add, remove, and retrieve version details. It works with strings representing gist IDs and version IDs, along with timestamps and metadata. Concrete use cases include synchronizing local gist versions with a remote server and parsing version metadata from gist names.
